name: Black Phoebe
overview: Sit in open on low perches to look for insects.They pump tails when perched. Can often keep up a string of sharp chip calls. They are non-migratory and are of least concern.
habitat: Dapper flycatchers from the western United States. Use mud to build cup-shaped nests against walls. Often near bodies of water from small streams to salt sprayed rocks and cliffs  of the pacific ocean.
